The paper deals with the security and efficiency of proof-of-work mechanisms in cryptocurrency systems, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also presents game-theoretic and economical analysis of the proposed protocols, which falls under the game theory (cs.GT) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the ecological impact of proof-of-work mechanisms, which could be considered under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
